      "name": "PASS Contracts",
      "type": "Table",
      "description": "Contract data that comes from the District of Columbia’s Procurement Automated Support System (PASS). The Office of Contracting and Procurement (OCP) is required to post contract awards valued at $100,000 or more for agencies served by OCP. The awarded contracts database includes a caption describing the type of goods or services provided, the contract number, the ordering agency, the contract amount, the period of time covered by the contract award, the contractor receiving the award, and the market type. To obtain a copy of any contract, you may submit a FOIA request onlinevia the DC government Public FOIA Portal. Questions regarding details within the data, contact the Office of Contract and Procurement at https://contracts.ocp.dc.gov/contact.",
